"Thought this be madness, yet there is method in't."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urandomuser.showPublicProfile?language=EN>random user</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(9/4/01 11:21:54 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I'll Take Mistwalkers for $200, Alex</span><hr size=1> I distinctly remember it is 50, as Celt, a ranger who used to be on our server, and I were messing around in sage (this was before Kunark came out and he was bored and wanted a runed cowl for his enchanter, and I was trying to make my way to safe hall to solo some when we met up in savant, which was fully popped, which was unusual because that was back when guk had over 100 people in it during prime time).  He was using his mistwalker and asked me what level I was.  I said 49, which I was at the time.  He said too bad, if I had been 50 he would have lent me the mistwalker but 49 was too low to proc so there was no point.<br>
<br>
- Xylem, E'ci <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubladari.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bladari</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(9/5/01 9:46:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I'll Take Mistwalkers for $200, Alex</span><hr size=1> Mistwalker Schimmy? Druel*, wish they still had that in game....yea that schimmy was nerfed big time, proced lvl 44, had 1hp hit for 144 dmg or so....Used to be able to proc the pet, and have a cleric on stand by to buff the pet once it was proc'd making it once bad arse killing machine.<br>
<br>
<br>
*sigh, wish verant wouldnt take out fun items like that out of game =P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upinepath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pinepath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(9/6/01 8:36:28 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Mistwalker</span><hr size=1> As I remember, it has always been a L50 proc, and always a 1hp doggie hitting for like 140.<br>
<br>
Then folks started buffing it after it procced, and it would survive for quite a while, and be a nice pet.<br>
<br>
nerf 1, MW pet no longer able to be buffed.<br>
<br>
Well, even without buffs, sometimes it wouldn't be attacked and die, and would get in more hits than they wanted, so...<br>
<br>
nerf 2, MW pet was uber-aggro, mobs would immediately attack one when it popped, so it would die quickly.<br>
<br>
Of course, if a mob was feared, or just really low level so it died right away, doggie would still end up hanging around.  Pushed somewhat into exploit range by a group of folks with MW dueling before a big fight, to pre-spawn a pile of doggies, that would do Ok damage, and draw aggro until they were all dead.<br>
<br>
nerf 3, MW pet pops, does one attack sequence, hit or miss, and commits suicide immediately.  Now just basically a 1-shot damage proc.<br>
<br>
There were other minor nerfs too, with VI reducing way down, then somewhat raising proc rate, stealth removal of sword from Vox loot, probably others I've forgotten. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usekiraashdelane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sekira Ashdelane</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(9/11/01 6:43:09 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mistwalker</span><hr size=1>   Actually they used to drop from Lady Vox (not PoH).  Pre-nerf they were 1hp Level 45 dogs that had double attack and hit for around 150s.  You could /pet back off when you proced them (or proc them on a greenie) and buff the heck out of them.<br>
<br>
  Seveal nerfs then took place.  The Proc rate was drastically lowered, and buffs were changed  so that a pet with less than 20 hp could not receive a pet buff.<br>
<br>
  Finally the proc rate was restored to closer to it's original and the pet itself was changed so that it is summoned, attacks either in response to you being attacked or on command, and dies after one round of attacks.  The MoB doesn't have to attack the pet for it to die.  It gets one melee round and goes poof.<br>
<br>
  I had much fun surprising the hell out of folks in the Druid BotB on my server by pulling out the old Mistwalker :)<br>
